column80: George Philip Reinagle (born 1802, died Dec.6, 1835) was a painter of marine subjects and the son of Ramsay Richard Reinagle.

A number of lots belonged to Josiah Taylor and some of them are marked Taylor B or T...B, the meaning of which is unclear.  There are 14 lots marked with both initials and just four with either T or Taylor.  There is no doubt that T refers to Josiah Taylor, but In subsequent sales there is a Sir B Taylor who could possibly be the T B   It is unlikely that Josian Taylor was related to Sir B Taylor, but a connection cannot be completely ruled out.
